FBIS4-41449 "drsov122_m_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Tajikistan Peace Talks in Tehran Focus on Cease-Fire Agreement Peace Talks in Tehran Focus on Cease-Fire Agreement LD2306153294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1256 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306153294 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The participants in the inter-Tajik talks which began in Tehran on June 18 are concentrating on the discussion of a cease-fire agreement and on measures to prevent other hostile actions. The draft was proposed by the UN special envoy Ramiro Piriz Ballon, the Russian Foreign Ministry's spokesman Grigoriy Karasin told journalists on Thursday. Karasin believes that the discussion and adoption of the agreement is the main goal of the Tehran talks and said that Russia hopes both Tajik delegations will reach an understanding on the issue. He also said that Russia would continue to assist the attainment of mutually acceptable agreements. "Our attitude to the parties concerned will depend on how sincerely they approach the talks," he said.
